The `css()` method in jQuery is used to get or set the CSS properties of HTML elements. It allows developers to modify the style dynamically at runtime, providing flexibility in styling the elements based on interactions or conditions.

Key Uses:

○ Get CSS Properties: Retrieve the current value of a specific CSS property

○ Set CSS Properties: Apply a single CSS property or multiple properties to selected elements dynamically

○ Chaining Capabilities: Use with other jQuery methods for streamlined code execution

Syntax:
```javascript
// To get the value of a property
$(selector).css(propertyName);

// To set a single property
$(selector).css(propertyName, value);

// To set multiple properties
$(selector).css({
    propertyName1: value1,
    propertyName2: value2,
    ...
});
```

